articles.author: Tetsushi Kajimoto, Leika Kihara
articles.description: Japan's economy contracted in July-September, snapping two straight quarters of expansion on soft consumption and exports, complicating the central bank's efforts to gradually phase out its massive monetary stimulus amid rising inflation.
articles.title: Japan's economy contracts as recession risks grow

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's October economic activity perked up as industrial output grew at a faster pace and retail sales growth beat expectations, an encouraging sign for an economy still showing significant pockets of weakness despite a flurry of support measures.
articles.title: China factory output, retail sales beat expectations in boost to economic recovery

articles.author: Joseph White
articles.description: The next generation of the Toyota Camry, the best-selling sedan in the U.S. market, will come with only a gas-electric hybrid powertrain, the boldest move yet by the Japanese automaker to push hybrid technology into the heart of the U.S. market.
articles.title: Toyota's Camry, best-selling car in US, goes all-hybrid

articles.author: Wayne Cole
articles.description: Australian wages posted the largest increase on record last quarter as a sharp rise in minimum wages benefited millions of workers, while intense competition among employers pushed up many individual pay deals.
articles.title: Australia wages see record rise in Q3, unlikely to be repeated

articles.author: Gilles Guillaume
articles.description: Renault (RENA.PA) will try on Wednesday to fire up doubtful investors ahead of a planned market listing of its electric vehicle (EV) unit Ampere, a key plank of CEO Luca de Meo's revamp of the French automaker.
articles.title: Renault seeks to charge up investors for EV unit IPO

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's central bank ramped up liquidity injection but kept the interest rate unchanged when rolling over maturing medium-term policy loans on Wednesday, matching market expectations.
articles.title: China c.bank boosts liquidity injection through policy loan, rate unchanged

articles.author: Marine Strauss
articles.description: Belgium has decided to temporarily ban the use of Novo Nordisk's (NOVOb.CO) diabetes drug Ozempic as a weight loss treatment amid a shortage of the medicine, according to a royal decree published in the country's Official Gazette on Tuesday.
articles.title: Belgium bans use of Ozempic for weight loss until summer

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: The Israeli military said it was carrying out an operation against Hamas in the Gaza Strip's Al Shifa hospital on Wednesday and urged all members of the militant group in the hospital to surrender.
articles.title: Israel raids Gaza's Al Shifa Hospital

articles.author: David Morgan, Richard Cowan
articles.description: U.S. House Speaker Mike Johnson will brave opposition from fellow Republicans and rely on Democratic votes on Tuesday in a risky tactic to avert a government shutdown.
articles.title: US House Speaker Johnson looks to Democrats to avert gov't shutdown

articles.author: Keith Coffman
articles.description: A 24-year-old man initially ruled incompetent to stand trial on charges that he fatally shot 10 people inside a Colorado grocery store in 2021, but later deemed mentally fit, pleaded not guilty by reason of insanity to murder charges on Tuesday.
articles.title: Suspect in Colorado supermarket massacre enters insanity plea
